So in your opinion rounded corners are outdated? I am this opinion too, but as it seems `Microsoft` is not. Because if in `CTChartSpace` the `RoundedCorners` is not set, then it is `true`by default.

But fortunately we can set it as needed using following method:

    private static void setRoundedCorners(XSSFChart chart, boolean setVal) {
        if (chart.getCTChartSpace().getRoundedCorners() == null) chart.getCTChartSpace().addNewRoundedCorners();
        chart.getCTChartSpace().getRoundedCorners().setVal(setVal);
    }

Using the current Apache POI versions, which are using `XDDF` for charts, this also can be:

    private static void setRoundedCorners(XDDFChart chart, boolean setVal) {
        if (chart.getCTChartSpace().getRoundedCorners() == null) chart.getCTChartSpace().addNewRoundedCorners();
        chart.getCTChartSpace().getRoundedCorners().setVal(setVal);
    }


Complete Example:


Get any chart example from https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/poi/trunk/poi-examples/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/examples/xssf/usermodel/ and then call

    setRoundedCorners(chart, false);

after chart creating.

